    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <head>30. National Security Action Memorandum No. 299<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d30fn1">Source: National Archives and Records Administration, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, <gloss target="#t_SPC1">S/PC</gloss>
                        Files: Lot 70 D 199, National Security Action Memos (<gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>). Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-05-12">May 12, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Evacuation and Protection of U.S. Citizens in Danger Areas Abroad</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has rescinded <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 6019/1
                    (Evacuation and Protection of U.S. Citizens in Danger Areas Abroad) dated
                    January 2, 1961<note n="2" xml:id="d30fn2">Regarding <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 6019/1, see <ref target="frus1958-60v03#pg_532">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1958–1960, vol. III, p.
                            532</ref>.</note> and has directed that the Secretaries of State and
                    Defense be responsible for carrying out this program.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
